Package: Holiday
Title: Festive Palettes and Visualization Themes for ggplot2
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Kaylen", "Ton", , "kaylent2k@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The 'Holiday' package provides festive color palettes, plot themes, 
    and fun date-based utilities for data visualizations inspired by popular holidays. 
    'Holiday' makes it easy to style ggplot2 graphics with seasonal colors and moods 
    such as Christmas, Valentineâ€™s Day, Halloween, Easter, Lunar New Year, and more. 
    Users can access custom color palettes through 'holiday_palette()', apply themed 
    ggplot2 styles with 'theme_holiday()', and even check how many days remain until 
    a given holiday using 'holiday_countdown()'. Additional features, such as 
    'plot_countdown()', visualize upcoming holidays in a cheerful and colorful way. 
    The package aims to bring creativity and festivity to data storytelling all year round.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5)
Imports: 
    ggplot2,
    grDevices,
    methods,
    scales
